---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy of Digital Runners in accordance with the revDSG and GDPR."
>
  <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-blue-950 text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Digital Runners</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-slate prose-lg">

      <p>
        The protection of your personal data is important to us. This privacy policy informs you
        about what data we collect, how we use it and what rights you have. It applies in
        accordance with the revised Swiss Data Protection Act (revDSG) and, where applicable, the
        EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
      </p>

      <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The party responsible for data processing on this website is:<br /><br />
        Digital Runners<br />
        [Street and number]<br />
        [Postcode] [City]<br />
        Switzerland<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:info@digital-runners.ch">info@digital-runners.ch</a>
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data Collected and Purpose</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Server log data</h3>
      <p>
        When you visit our website, the following data is automatically recorded in server log
        files by the hosting provider:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address of the requesting device (anonymised)</li>
        <li>Date and time of the request</li>
        <li>URL accessed</li>
        <li>HTTP status code</li>
        <li>Amount of data transferred</li>
        <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is used solely to ensure the technical operation of the website and is not used
        to identify individual persons. The legal basis is our legitimate interest
        (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 Contact form</h3>
      <p>
        If you use our contact form, the following information is processed:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Content of your message</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We use this data exclusively to process your enquiry. It is not passed on to third
        parties. The legal basis is consent and the initiation of a contract (Art. 6(1)(a) and
        (b) GDPR). Data from contact enquiries is deleted after the enquiry has been resolved,
        unless statutory retention obligations apply.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This website does not use tracking cookies or third-party analytics tools. No personal
        data is collected or shared for marketing purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted via <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>. Cloudflare is a US-based
        company. When you access the website, your requests are routed through the Cloudflare
        network. For more information on data protection at Cloudflare, please visit{' '}
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          cloudflare.com/privacypolicy
        </a>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification</strong> of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure</strong> of your data, unless statutory retention obligations apply</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction</strong> of processing</li>
        <li><strong>Data portability</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise your rights, please contact us by email at:{' '}
        <a href="mailto:info@digital-runners.ch">info@digital-runners.ch</a>
      </p>

      <h2>6. Right to Lodge a Complaint</h2>
      <p>
        You have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent data protection authority. In
        Switzerland, this is the Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner (FDPIC):{' '}
        <a href="https://www.edoeb.admin.ch/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.edoeb.admin.ch</a>
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update this privacy policy as necessary. The current version is
        always available on this page.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: February 2026</p>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
